# Hierarchy Page Redesign — Simplified Tabbed Approach

## Problem
The current hierarchy page uses a **tree sidebar + detail panel** that expands 5 levels (Region → District → Complex → Building → Floor). This is overwhelming for admins who mainly manage Regions and Districts.

## Proposed Design

Replace with a **tabbed CrudPage** using the same pill-tab bar as Property Config:

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Location Hierarchy                                      │
│  [Regions] [Districts] [Complexes] [Buildings] [Floors]  │  ← pill tabs
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Regions                              [+ Add]  🔍        │
│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐      │
│  │  Name              │  Districts  │  Actions    │      │
│  ├────────────────────┼─────────────┼─────────────┤      │
│  │  Tashkent          │  12         │  ✏️ 🗑      │      │
│  │  Samarkand         │  8          │  ✏️ 🗑      │      │
│  └────────────────────┴─────────────┴─────────────┘      │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Districts tab shows a **Region filter dropdown** to scope results.

## Files to Change

### [MODIFY] [HierarchyPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/user/Maydon/web/admin-panel/src/pages/HierarchyPage.tsx)
- Complete rewrite: tabbed layout with pill-style tabs (Regions, Districts, Complexes, Buildings, Floors)
- Each tab = CrudPage with appropriate columns and forms
- Districts tab includes Region filter dropdown
- Same pill-tab CSS as PropertyConfigPage

